        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">@[simp]</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">lemma</span> <span class=\"n\">simple_graph.from_rel_adj</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">V</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">r</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span> <span class=\"bp\">→</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span> <span class=\"bp\">→</span> <span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">v</span> <span class=\"n\">w</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">simple_graph.from_rel</span> <span class=\"n\">r</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">adj</span> <span class=\"n\">v</span> <span class=\"n\">w</span> <span class=\"bp\">↔</span> <span class=\"n\">v</span> <span class=\"bp\">≠</span> <span class=\"n\">w</span> <span class=\"bp\">∧</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">r</span> <span class=\"n\">v</span> <span class=\"n\">w</span> <span class=\"bp\">∨</span> <span class=\"n\">r</span> <span class=\"n\">w</span> <span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"n\">iff.rfl</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is it possible to make <code>∨</code> look less similar to <code>v</code> on VS Code? does anyone know a trick?</p>",
