    {
        "content": "<p>The vscode extension recommends this setting:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Fonts with good Unicode support: <code>\"editor.fontFamily\": \"Source Code Pro Medium, DejaVu Sans Mono\"</code>. Note that for this configuration to work properly, both fonts must be specified in this order (so that characters that are not available in Source Code Pro are rendered using DejaVu Sans Mono).</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 259204225,
        "sender_full_name": "Gabriel Ebner",
        "timestamp": 1635321607
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But the two characters still look similar even with these fonts.  But don't worry, it gets better with time.  Just wait until you see <code>→</code> and <code>⟶</code>.</p>",
